Both outputs are written and validated.

**`transcript.json`** — 15 iterations, 37 hypotheses, 35 analyses, validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative walkthrough.

Headline finding: response is dominated by a combinatorial subgroup. Patients with `feature_013=0 AND feature_008=1` (n=9039, 18% of cohort) have ~80% baseline response. Within that subgroup, any one of three "treatments" (`feature_015`, `feature_021`, `feature_027`) collapses response to ~17% (risk diff −62.7 pp, OR 0.052). Outside the subgroup the same treatments have essentially no effect (|risk diff| < 0.01). Treatment prevalence is balanced across the (f013, f008) cells, so the heterogeneity is genuine effect modification, not channeling. Both predicates are necessary — flipping either `feature_013=1` or `feature_008=0` is enough to suppress the treatment effect.
